  "text": "Neurological deficit was examined at 24 h after reperfusion and scored on a 4-point scale according to the method described by Bederson's group [CITATION_1] . The changes observed in the neurological deficit scores of the different groups are shown in Fig. 2 . Rats treated with aspirin (group 3) for 30 days after MCAO exhibited a moderate reduction in their neurobehavioral scores compared with the sham-operated group at 24 h after ischemia (P = 0.0525). However, rats treated with TRCQT alone (group 4) for 30 days showed a significant reduction in their neurobehavioral deficit score compared with the sham-operated group at 24 h after thromboembolic occlusion (P = 0.0537). Notably, rats treated with a",
